♪ You're the last to know. ♪

280
00:14:15,338 --> 00:14:17,856
Nic.

281
00:14:21,695 --> 00:14:22,695
Nic.

282
00:14:24,698 --> 00:14:25,863
Not funny.

283
00:14:25,932 --> 00:14:29,650
Nic.

284
00:14:29,719 --> 00:14:32,103
Acute leukemic on chemo.

285
00:14:32,171 --> 00:14:33,716
Fiancé called because she
was shaking uncontrollably.

286
00:14:33,740 --> 00:14:35,718
Uh, she spiked a fever
this morning, 100.8.

287
00:14:35,742 --> 00:14:37,074
Also, there was some vomiting.

288
00:14:37,143 --> 00:14:38,610
There's no blood in it.

289
00:14:38,678 --> 00:14:39,772
Last chemo was a week ago.

290
00:14:39,796 --> 00:14:42,062
Hey.

291
00:14:42,131 --> 00:14:43,598
You're here.

292
00:14:43,667 --> 00:14:44,815
I was scared.

293
00:14:44,885 --> 00:14:46,484
Ah, you're running a fever.

294
00:14:46,552 --> 00:14:48,169
It's just another infection.

295
00:14:48,237 --> 00:14:50,232
Chemo is still crushing
your immune system.

296
00:14:50,256 --> 00:14:53,224
We'll get you started on broad-
spectrum antibiotics again.

297
00:14:53,293 --> 00:14:55,826
Acetaminophen to
get your fever down.

298
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:57,855
Get cultures from
both arms. Urine.

299
00:14:57,897 --> 00:14:58,979
She'll need a head CT.

300
00:14:59,048 --> 00:15:02,199
- Okay.
- Don't worry.

301
00:15:02,269 --> 00:15:03,834
We'll get this under control.

302
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:05,419
Get you both back home soon.

303
00:15:05,488 --> 00:15:07,521
You're in good hands.

304
00:15:07,590 --> 00:15:09,590
Guess where he
went to medical school.

305
00:15:10,610 --> 00:15:14,778
I think he went to
Harvard Medical School.

306
00:15:14,831 --> 00:15:17,715
Was it Harvard Medical School?

307
00:15:17,784 --> 00:15:21,802
I'm pretty sure it was
Harvard Medical School.

308
00:15:21,871 --> 00:15:23,303
Lily means a lot to all of us.

309
00:15:23,373 --> 00:15:24,950
She's been in and
out of the ER so often,

310
00:15:24,974 --> 00:15:28,325
we're all invested, but her
diagnosis is a tough one.

311
00:15:28,394 --> 00:15:29,827
I'm giving you a gift.

312
00:15:29,896 --> 00:15:31,929
From now on, she's your patient.

313
00:15:31,998 --> 00:15:34,582
But if you screw this
one up, I will wreck you.

314
00:15:34,651 --> 00:15:36,767
- I got it.
- Hey, Conrad.

315
00:15:40,607 --> 00:15:42,590
What's wrong?

316
00:15:42,658 --> 00:15:44,537
Your appendectomy patient
who had surgery last night...

317
00:15:44,561 --> 00:15:45,726
What about him?

318
00:15:45,795 --> 00:15:48,812
Conrad, he's dead.

319
00:15:48,865 --> 00:15:50,715
What the hell happened?

320
00:15:50,784 --> 00:15:52,800
HODAD happened.

321
00:16:06,232 --> 00:16:08,599
What was it this time, Bell?

322
00:16:08,668 --> 00:16:09,934
Pulmonary embolism?

323
00:16:10,003 --> 00:16:11,852
Undisclosed heart condition.

324
00:16:11,921 --> 00:16:15,256
Tragic situation, and
naturally I covered for you.

325
00:16:15,325 --> 00:16:16,740
You need to consider a change

326
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:18,220
before you kill
any more patients.

327
00:16:18,244 --> 00:16:19,910
How dare you?

328
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,357
Go be one of those
celebrity TV doctors.

329
00:16:21,381 --> 00:16:22,880
You look the part.

330
00:16:22,932 --> 00:16:24,972
Make a lot of money,
wear nice clothes.

331
00:16:25,018 --> 00:16:26,884
You'd be great at it.

332
00:16:26,953 --> 00:16:29,586
You watch yourself, Conrad.

333
00:16:29,656 --> 00:16:32,222
You know, I'm remembering
a pretty, young resident

334
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:34,909
that reported a fatal chemo
overdose a couple years back.

335
00:16:34,977 --> 00:16:38,278
That good deed...
that led to a lawsuit

336
00:16:38,347 --> 00:16:39,914
that cost the hospital millions.

337
00:16:39,982 --> 00:16:42,099
You tell me, Conrad,
where is she today?

338
00:16:42,168 --> 00:16:43,813
With cutting-edge research.

339
00:16:43,837 --> 00:16:45,697
At this moment, our
patients are involved

340
00:16:45,721 --> 00:16:47,121
in over 100...

341
00:16:47,190 --> 00:16:49,256
Not here.

342
00:16:53,496 --> 00:16:56,296
♪ Gonna be here all my life ♪

343
00:16:56,365 --> 00:16:58,043
♪ But I don't know
what else to do... ♪

344
00:16:58,067 --> 00:17:00,951
How'd you get that
cheeseburger, Chad?

345
00:17:01,021 --> 00:17:02,970
Delivery app.

346
00:17:03,056 --> 00:17:05,890
It looks like you haven't
been following your diet.

347
00:17:05,942 --> 00:17:07,758
Diets don't work.

348
00:17:07,811 --> 00:17:08,954
Have you been
taking your insulin?

349
00:17:08,978 --> 00:17:11,795
I don't want a lecture, Nic.

350
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:14,832
I'm here 'cause
my toe's killing me.

351
00:17:19,005 --> 00:17:21,572
Severe gangrene.

352
00:17:22,858 --> 00:17:25,226
♪ All I know ♪

353
00:17:25,294 --> 00:17:28,979
♪ Hear me on the radio ♪

354
00:17:29,049 --> 00:17:31,026
♪ But I keep thinking
the time will go... ♪

355
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:33,900
The toe was already
dead. I just touched it.

356
00:17:36,005 --> 00:17:36,937
He broke my toe!

357
00:17:37,006 --> 00:17:38,138
His toe fell off.

358
00:17:38,207 --> 00:17:40,235
Chad, buddy, we are
amputating the whole foot.

359
00:17:40,259 --> 00:17:42,960
You knew this was coming. Devon.

360
00:17:43,012 --> 00:17:45,052
What do you think
they got for dessert?

361
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:48,615
You can't keep me here!

362
00:17:48,685 --> 00:17:49,862
- You need to settle down.
- Calm down.

363
00:17:49,886 --> 00:17:51,618
- Get me out!
- Calm down.

364
00:17:51,688 --> 00:17:52,820
New admission.

365
00:17:52,889 --> 00:17:55,690
21-year-old girl,
history of IV drug use.

366
00:17:55,775 --> 00:17:57,491
Likely endo.

367
00:17:57,577 --> 00:17:59,021
She was trying
to steal Dilaudid.

368
00:17:59,045 --> 00:18:00,277
Now she wants to leave AMA.

369
00:18:00,346 --> 00:18:01,790
She's been spiking
fever, vomiting.

370
00:18:01,814 --> 00:18:03,175
- She's using again.
- Hey, hey.

371
00:18:03,199 --> 00:18:04,777
She took all my money
and spent it on oxy.

372
00:18:04,801 --> 00:18:06,011
Oy, listen to me.

373
00:18:06,035 --> 00:18:08,301
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
- Please, stop.

374
00:18:08,370 --> 00:18:10,021
Hey, hey, hey. See these?

375
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:11,984
See these? These
are Osler's nodes

376
00:18:12,008 --> 00:18:13,986
caused by bacteria
swarming in your blood

377
00:18:14,010 --> 00:18:15,104
and moving throughout your body.

378
00:18:15,128 --> 00:18:17,061
Classic for endocarditis,

379
00:18:17,130 --> 00:18:18,340
an infection of the heart valve.

380
00:18:18,364 --> 00:18:20,681
Happens to drug
users all the time.

381
00:18:20,750 --> 00:18:22,928
If you walk out of here
without any antibiotics,

382
00:18:22,952 --> 00:18:24,752
this will kill you.

383
00:18:24,821 --> 00:18:28,955
If you give us a chance,
we can save your life.

384
00:18:29,025 --> 00:18:32,894
I'll stay if you give me
three milligrams of Dilaudid.

385
00:18:32,962 --> 00:18:36,063
Two.

386
00:18:36,149 --> 00:18:39,984
If you calm down and you
get back in bed right now.

387
00:18:49,946 --> 00:18:52,012
Chloe, baby!

388
00:18:52,081 --> 00:18:55,015
- Get a crash cart.
- Chloe, baby!

389
00:18:55,084 --> 00:18:56,946
- I'm not getting a pulse.
- Code Blue in ED alpha!

390
00:18:56,970 --> 00:18:58,280
- Get them out of here.
- No, no!

391
00:18:58,304 --> 00:19:00,587
- Baby, no! No!
- You need to give them space.

392
00:19:00,673 --> 00:19:02,735
Start compressions.
You're running the code.

393
00:19:02,759 --> 00:19:03,924
I've never run a code.

394
00:19:04,010 --> 00:19:05,738
- Do you want an amp of bicarb?
- He's in charge.

395
00:19:05,762 --> 00:19:08,095
Page Anesthesia.

396
00:19:10,850 --> 00:19:13,284
What is the first question
you ask in a code?

397
00:19:13,352 --> 00:19:16,253
Rhythm.

398
00:19:16,322 --> 00:19:17,738
What's her rhythm?

399
00:19:17,824 --> 00:19:18,956
P.E.A.

400
00:19:20,527 --> 00:19:22,721
- Should we shock?
- No, we can't. Her rhythm's not shockable.

401
00:19:22,745 --> 00:19:24,825
Get me one of epi.
Make those compressions

402
00:19:24,864 --> 00:19:25,962
harder and faster.

403
00:19:26,032 --> 00:19:27,072
Prepare to intubate.

404
00:19:35,458 --> 00:19:38,025
It's been 24 minutes.

405
00:19:38,094 --> 00:19:40,094
- It's time to call the code.
- No!

406
00:19:40,162 --> 00:19:42,613
This is my code. You
gave me this code.

407
00:19:42,682 --> 00:19:46,150
She's 21 years old.

408
00:19:46,219 --> 00:19:48,852
Harder, man. You need
to feel the ribs crack.

409
00:19:51,858 --> 00:19:53,291
That's enough.

410
00:19:53,359 --> 00:19:56,376
No. Move.

411
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:57,979
I'm not giving up.

412
00:19:59,399 --> 00:20:02,116
I said that's enough.

413
00:20:17,233 --> 00:20:19,200
We got a pulse.

414
00:20:21,287 --> 00:20:23,470
You saved her life.

415
00:20:31,947 --> 00:20:35,799
Her end tidal CO2 was less
than 15 for the entire code.

416
00:20:35,852 --> 00:20:38,152
- That doesn't necessarily mean that...
- Yes.

417
00:20:38,221 --> 00:20:39,987
Yes, it does.

418
00:20:40,056 --> 00:20:42,001
She's been without oxygen
to her brain for 26 minutes.

419
00:20:42,025 --> 00:20:44,625
Congratulations, you got
her heart beating again,

420
00:20:44,693 --> 00:20:45,959
but she's brain-dead.

421
00:21:02,411 --> 00:21:06,063
You came in here all
bright-eyed and bushy-tailed,

422
00:21:06,132 --> 00:21:08,443
ready to save lives, but
today you didn't save a life.

423
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:12,019
You saved a brain stem
because you didn't listen to me.

424
00:21:12,087 --> 00:21:14,654
Now the repercussions
on Chloe's family

425
00:21:14,723 --> 00:21:18,075
will be catastrophic.

426
00:21:18,144 --> 00:21:20,144
There's no way
they'll accept this.

427
00:21:20,212 --> 00:21:22,324
Chloe looks alive. They'll
think she can wake up.

428
00:21:22,348 --> 00:21:26,183
So they will hover over
her, tend to her for days,

429
00:21:26,235 --> 00:21:28,475
weeks, maybe years,
waiting for a miracle to happen

430
00:21:28,537 --> 00:21:31,955
that's utterly impossible.

431
00:21:32,024 --> 00:21:35,075
What was rule one, Devon?

432
00:21:35,161 --> 00:21:38,062
Do whatever you tell me to do.

433
00:21:38,131 --> 00:21:39,597
No questions asked.

434
00:21:39,665 --> 00:21:42,165
All we want to do
is help our patients,

435
00:21:42,234 --> 00:21:44,112
but what they don't
teach us in medical school

436
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:46,136
is there are so many
ways to do harm.

437
00:22:07,926 --> 00:22:12,062
As you can see, the
Titian is an amazing piece

438
00:22:12,115 --> 00:22:13,514
of medical technology.

439
00:22:13,583 --> 00:22:17,084
We've nicknamed
it the "Hand of God"

440
00:22:17,170 --> 00:22:21,088
because it does what no
human hands could accomplish.

441
00:22:21,156 --> 00:22:23,891
Even yours?

442
00:22:23,959 --> 00:22:25,325
Yeah, even mine.

443
00:22:27,296 --> 00:22:30,230
The finest surgeon in the world

444
00:22:30,299 --> 00:22:32,532
would benefit from the Titian.

445
00:22:32,601 --> 00:22:33,934
It's capable

446
00:22:34,020 --> 00:22:37,070
of movements that are incredibly

447
00:22:37,140 --> 00:22:39,573
steady and precise,

448
00:22:39,641 --> 00:22:42,475
virtually eliminating
human error.

449
00:22:42,544 --> 00:22:45,162
Chastain Park Memorial

450
00:22:45,231 --> 00:22:48,265
is the first hospital
in the country

451
00:22:48,317 --> 00:22:50,701
to have this miraculous machine,

452
00:22:50,770 --> 00:22:53,136
thanks to Dr. Bell,
who spearheaded

453
00:22:53,205 --> 00:22:54,555
this fund-raising campaign,

454
00:22:54,623 --> 00:22:57,358
and, of course, to you,
our very generous donors.

455
00:22:57,443 --> 00:23:00,060
Thank you.

456
00:23:02,247 --> 00:23:05,582
"Serious complications
may occur,

457
00:23:05,651 --> 00:23:09,486
"up to and including death.

458
00:23:09,555 --> 00:23:12,506
Individual surgical
results may vary."

459
00:23:12,575 --> 00:23:13,718
I've trained for
months to do this.

460
00:23:13,742 --> 00:23:15,375
Results will not vary.

461
00:23:15,444 --> 00:23:18,278
Until Bell gets his hands on it.

462
00:23:18,347 --> 00:23:19,630
Over my dead body.

463
00:23:19,699 --> 00:23:21,376
I'm sure HODAD
could manage that.

464
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:23,166
I heard a nurse call him HODAD.

465
00:23:23,235 --> 00:23:24,835
What does it stand for?

466
00:23:24,904 --> 00:23:28,838
Hands of Death and Destruction.

467
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:31,141
You're kidding. Does
that mean everyone knows

468
00:23:31,210 --> 00:23:32,410
about his complication rate?

469
00:23:32,445 --> 00:23:35,379
All the nurses,
some of the doctors.

470
00:23:35,448 --> 00:23:37,014
The ones who pay attention.

471
00:23:39,468 --> 00:23:41,401
Poetry.

472
00:23:41,470 --> 00:23:44,171
But none of the
patients. They're clueless.

473
00:23:44,257 --> 00:23:48,325
You've got the best
hands in the business,

474
00:23:48,394 --> 00:23:50,355
but he's still the most
requested surgeon

475
00:23:50,379 --> 00:23:52,229
in the hospital.

476
00:23:52,298 --> 00:23:54,026
Have you seen
his reviews online?

477
00:23:54,050 --> 00:23:56,567
He has got five stars.

478
00:23:58,487 --> 00:24:01,672
Top patient review:
"McDreamy is real."

479
00:24:01,740 --> 00:24:04,324
- You want to hear yours?
- Don't care.

480
00:24:04,393 --> 00:24:06,377
You got one star.

481
00:24:06,445 --> 00:24:08,062
"Steer clear of Dr. Okafor.

482
00:24:08,130 --> 00:24:10,397
She told me my uterus sucked."

483
00:24:10,483 --> 00:24:13,317
It did suck.

484
00:24:16,138 --> 00:24:18,338
I just had hernia
surgery with Dr. Bell.

485
00:24:18,407 --> 00:24:20,307
The man has magic hands.

486
00:24:24,513 --> 00:24:26,124
Dr. Flores, dial 182...

487
00:24:26,148 --> 00:24:27,276
Hey.

488
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:30,117
Randolph, I'm so
glad you're here.

489
00:24:31,320 --> 00:24:33,787
Where else would I be?

490
00:24:33,855 --> 00:24:35,467
You better finish up
those smoked oysters.

491
00:24:35,491 --> 00:24:36,990
There's no food after midnight.

492
00:24:37,059 --> 00:24:38,403
All right. They're
absolutely delicious.

493
00:24:38,427 --> 00:24:41,444
This whole VIP
floor is spectacular.

494
00:24:41,514 --> 00:24:44,764
It's nothing more than
you deserve, my friend.

495
00:24:44,833 --> 00:24:46,528
If it hadn't been for
your generous donation,

496
00:24:46,552 --> 00:24:49,420
there would be no
new cancer wing.

497
00:24:49,488 --> 00:24:52,272
- Well...
- So...

498
00:24:52,358 --> 00:24:53,668
I hear you're gonna
be the first patient

499
00:24:53,692 --> 00:24:55,025
to benefit from the Titian.

500
00:24:55,094 --> 00:24:56,476
Yeah, it's quite the honor.

501
00:24:56,545 --> 00:24:58,795
I hear the damn thing
practically operates itself.

502
00:24:58,864 --> 00:25:01,632
Have you met your
surgeon yet, Dr. Okafor?

503
00:25:01,701 --> 00:25:03,400
Nope, not yet.

504
00:25:03,469 --> 00:25:05,301
She's Nigerian.

505
00:25:05,371 --> 00:25:07,304
Mm-hmm.

506
00:25:07,373 --> 00:25:08,839
Yeah, here on a visa.

507
00:25:08,908 --> 00:25:10,807
Very promising young resident.

508
00:25:12,310 --> 00:25:13,522
What do you mean,
"young resident"?

509
00:25:13,546 --> 00:25:16,079
Well, second year, I believe.

510
00:25:16,132 --> 00:25:19,099
Randolph, I spoke
directly to the CEO...

511
00:25:19,168 --> 00:25:21,468
I mentioned you...
But she told me

512
00:25:21,537 --> 00:25:23,103
that Dr. Okafor was the best

513
00:25:23,172 --> 00:25:25,723
possible person to remove
my prostate with the Titian.

514
00:25:25,791 --> 00:25:26,952
She'll be fine,
I'm fairly certain.

515
00:25:26,976 --> 00:25:28,442
I want you.

516
00:25:28,511 --> 00:25:29,843
You're the chief of surgery.

517
00:25:29,911 --> 00:25:31,522
Don't you think I
deserve the best?

518
00:25:31,546 --> 00:25:33,847
Yes.

519
00:25:33,916 --> 00:25:36,499
And I'll make sure you get it.

520
00:25:36,569 --> 00:25:38,501
Thank you.

521
00:25:38,571 --> 00:25:40,665
You have a visitor
in the main lobby.

