00:25:40,689 --> 00:25:42,773
Lisa brought this
back to you, baby,

523
00:25:42,841 --> 00:25:44,191
your honey bunny.

524
00:25:44,259 --> 00:25:47,461
I'm so happy
you're with us again.

525
00:25:47,529 --> 00:25:49,512
I'll be right back, my darling.

526
00:25:49,582 --> 00:25:50,781
Dr. Pravesh,

527
00:25:50,850 --> 00:25:52,399
I never thanked you

528
00:25:52,468 --> 00:25:55,336
for saving my daughter's life.

529
00:25:55,404 --> 00:25:57,854
Thank you.

530
00:25:57,923 --> 00:26:00,290
You're wonderful.

531
00:26:00,359 --> 00:26:02,626
I'll be in the cafeteria
if she wakes up.

532
00:26:16,058 --> 00:26:17,490
You okay?

533
00:26:17,559 --> 00:26:20,860
Nothing like this has ever
happened to me before.

534
00:26:20,929 --> 00:26:22,223
They'll do an
investigation, right?

535
00:26:22,247 --> 00:26:23,546
Are you kidding me?

536
00:26:23,616 --> 00:26:25,526
The hospital will
probably give you a medal.

537
00:26:25,550 --> 00:26:28,518
Every day Chloe's in the ICU,

538
00:26:28,588 --> 00:26:29,987
they bill thousands of dollars.

539
00:26:30,056 --> 00:26:32,522
It's a huge payday for them.

540
00:26:32,592 --> 00:26:36,226
Medicine isn't practiced
by saints, Devon.

541
00:26:36,295 --> 00:26:38,328
It's a business.

542
00:26:38,381 --> 00:26:41,481
Yeah, but this, all this,
just isn't what I imagined.

543
00:26:41,550 --> 00:26:43,984
Then you're lucky.

544
00:26:45,437 --> 00:26:49,540
When I was 13, my mom
went in for her routine physical.

545
00:26:49,608 --> 00:26:52,543
They did some tests, and they...

546
00:26:52,611 --> 00:26:55,929
they found something
small on her lung.

547
00:26:55,997 --> 00:26:58,382
So they cracked her chest,

548
00:26:58,450 --> 00:27:00,751
and her lung collapsed.

549
00:27:00,819 --> 00:27:03,052
She got pneumonia,
and five days later,

550
00:27:03,121 --> 00:27:05,355
she was dead.

551
00:27:05,424 --> 00:27:06,807
She was 38 years old.

552
00:27:08,643 --> 00:27:10,594
I'm so sorry.

553
00:27:10,662 --> 00:27:14,014
This happens all
the time, Devon.

554
00:27:14,082 --> 00:27:16,633
Medical error is the third-
leading cause of death

555
00:27:16,702 --> 00:27:20,286
in the United States after
cancer and heart disease.

556
00:27:21,590 --> 00:27:23,452
They don't want us
talking about that.

557
00:27:23,476 --> 00:27:27,394
But you still show
up here every day.

558
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:30,413
'Cause it's personal to me.

559
00:27:30,483 --> 00:27:32,403
And there are
still plenty of good

560
00:27:32,435 --> 00:27:37,437
doctors and nurses
trying to do the right thing.

561
00:27:37,523 --> 00:27:41,274
I'm just trying
to be one of 'em.

562
00:27:45,731 --> 00:27:47,463
Lily.

563
00:27:47,533 --> 00:27:50,266
You look like
you're feeling better.

564
00:27:50,336 --> 00:27:53,437
Yeah, yeah. Conrad's
a miracle worker.

565
00:27:53,505 --> 00:27:55,505
Well, good. Let's
get you back in bed.

566
00:27:55,541 --> 00:27:56,940
You need to stay warm.

567
00:28:00,463 --> 00:28:02,062
Where's your fiancé?

568
00:28:02,130 --> 00:28:04,665
Oh, he... he left
a few hours ago.

569
00:28:04,733 --> 00:28:06,116
I was still in the ER.

570
00:28:06,185 --> 00:28:08,601
I bet he's just exhausted.

571
00:28:08,688 --> 00:28:11,638
- He'll be back tomorrow, I'm sure.
- No, he won't.

572
00:28:13,609 --> 00:28:16,643
I got diagnosed a month
after I got engaged.

573
00:28:16,712 --> 00:28:19,480
It's not his fault. He
didn't sign up for cancer.

574
00:28:22,351 --> 00:28:25,152
I mean, maybe if I
just let him go sooner...

575
00:28:25,237 --> 00:28:28,038
I was selfish.

576
00:28:28,107 --> 00:28:29,789
Didn't want to die alone.

577
00:28:34,246 --> 00:28:36,196
Do you have to go right away?

578
00:28:37,399 --> 00:28:40,500
No.

579
00:28:40,586 --> 00:28:43,469
No. We can talk.

580
00:29:03,776 --> 00:29:05,825
Come on, man.

581
00:29:09,732 --> 00:29:12,132
Status?

